AB  - In this paper two major models of the gross-domestic product of four interacting nations are derived. One is an ordinary differential game of pursuit. The other is a hereditary one which utilizes the principle of rational expectations. A theory of interactions via net export is postulated. The UN and IMF data for a group of nations are Used to validate it, and test for competition and cooperation MATLAB and MAPLE programs are used. The consequences of cooperation and competition Lire studied. (c) 2004 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
